observations.recommendation:
We recommended the following measures to the Local Chief Executive to ensure the effective implementation of infrastructure projects:
Create a Local Monitoring Committee of which function shall include the monitoring of the implementation of the PPAs of the LGUs, from procurement to execution/construction, and payment;
Instruct the Municipal Engineer/MPDC and BAC to conduct extensive monitoring on the implementation of the contructed PPAs and to appropriately communicate all findings found during inspection which shall also include the actual percentage of completion so that the contractor can immediately request for payment in accordance with the IRR of RA 9184;
Require the BAC and Engineer/MPDC to conduct inspection within 24 hours upon receipt of the request from the Contractor and accurately reflect the work accomplishment and date of the conduct of inspection in the report; and
Require the Monitoring Committee, Engineer and BAC to sufficiently inform the LCE of the result of inspection and the Accountant to facilitate the payment accordingly and/or effect any deductions for liquidated damages or other sanctions thereto.

We recommend the following:
1. The Local Chief Executive (LCE) as a co-chairman and all other members of the Local School Board (LSB) to enact SEF Budget which shall be the basis for the utilization of Special Education Fund (SEF);
2. The Local Chief Executive (LCE) to ensure that all public schools within its jurisdiction should equally avail of the Special Education Fund (SEF) for the benefits of all public students thereof;
3. The Local Chief Executive (LCE) to improve the utilization of Special Education Fund (SEF) which definitely for the welfare of its constituents; and
4. The Municipal Accountant/ Treasurer to ensure that disbursement out of the Special Education Fund (SEF) must be pursuant to the budget prepared by the Local School Board.

2.10	We recommended that the Local Chief Executive and other concerned
		local officials direct the concerned officials including the respective               		department heads:
a.	to conduct an annual physical count of its Property, Plant, and                		Equipment;
b.	reflect the correct valuation of all its PPE;
c.	segregates the obsolete and unserviceable from the serviceable ones        		(and correspondingly appraise them and classify them under Other       		PPE);
d.	upon completion, reconcile the PPE Inventory and Other PPE                                                            		Inventory with the records of the Municipal Accountant and the            		designated Property Officer; and															 e.	initiate steps towards the disposal of the obsolete and unserviceable 		PPE classified and inventoried under Other PPE

8.18		To address the issues and concerns, we recommended the following:
a.	The Local Chief Executive (LCE) as a co-chairman and all other 		members of the Local School Board (LSB) shall prepare the SEF 		budget and pass the corresponding resolution for its approval as 		basis for the utilization of Special Education Fund (SEF);
b.	The Local Chief Executive (LCE) shall ensure that all public schools 		within its jurisdiction shall be equitably allocated the necessary 		amount for their individual operations and maintenance out of the 		Special Education Fund (SEF);
c.	The Local Chief Executive (LCE) in consultation with sectors 		involved shall devise ways and means to improve the fair and 		equitable allocation of SEF funds among the beneficiary schools and 		to make the funds available at the time they are needed by them; and
d.	The LCE shall direct the Municipal Accountant/ Treasurer to ensure 		that disbursement out of the Special Education Fund (SEF) shall be 		consistent with  the budget prepared by the Local School Board.

We reiterate our recommendations that the Local Chief Executive should:

Ensure that payment of infrastructure projects is supported with complete documentation in pursuance to PD 1445;

Make sure that all supporting documents are properly signed by appropriate officials
